  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Livelihoods in the Poorest Districts of the Mekong Delta</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project is the joint effort of Heifer Vietnam, local authorities and project partners in the Mekong Delta to assist poor households though applying Heifer&#x2019;s Value-Based Holistic Community Development (VBHCD) model. Participants will be selected who are interested in participating and committed to take initiative in improving their lives but have limited productive assets.  Priority will be given to poor, socially deprived and climate change affected households.  The project areas are the poorest districts in the poorest provinces of the Mekong Delta region. The families in these areas are struggling with limited land for production, illiteracy, unemployment, poor nutrition and lack of clean water and sanitation. The project will improve both physical and spiritual aspects of participating households&#x2019; lives, generate jobs, decrease poverty rate in the project sites and enhance community harmony.This project will assist 1,480 original families. Each family will receive one heifer, and either swine, goats, chicken, ducks or fingerlings based on each family&#x2019;s needs and local conditions. Each project member also receives 1 million VND for constructing an animal barn, grass seedling, vaccines, or environmental equipment (biogas, vermiculture, etc.) as well as trainings on both technical and non-technical issues such as livestock management, crop production, enterprise development, 12 cornerstones, VBHCD, PSRP, HIV/AIDS, etc. Another 2,835 families will be assisted through Passing on the Gift within the five year life of the project.After three years of project implementation, the families not only improve their livelihood but also are able to organize collective productions that align with market demands.The total direct cost budget of this project is 34,180,000,000 VND (US$ 1,627,619) of which 47% (US$ 763,095) will be contributed by the People&#x2019;s Committees of the five committed provinces.</narrative>
  </description>
